extendedInfo.description: Daddy511 is an easy to use contraction timer and pregnancy tracker.  Even tells parents when its time to go to the hospital!-511 analysis and contraction statistics-Provides number and directions to your defined hospital-Counts down the due date for your baby

reviews.title: Words can\'t express my gratitude
reviews.comment: Thank you so much to the makers of Daddy 511! Got us through contraction pre-hospital like a pro. I recommend tollerant mode for 1st child. Must have!
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Looks nice...but...
reviews.comment: Looks nice and is easy to use. Unfortunately I had some problems with it tracking rest times accurately when I was switching between apps. It almost seemed like it lost it place with some of the timings...
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Great help
reviews.comment: Used it for my first child, helped us answer the nurses questions and know when to go. Thanks
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.comment: avg display is hard to find. Interface for choosing hospital and Dr is poor. Export to Gdocs sheet would be nice. Also needs auto save.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Great app
reviews.comment: Only thing that could make it better is a widget with the timer on it! It has a widget but it only shows the baby\'s info. Will give 5 stars if you add the widget!
reviews.author: Amanda Conaway

reviews.title: Bug bug bugs
reviews.comment: Why when app closes, must the contraction details be lost? Have u considered programming it to calculate the difference between time stamps instead of using a real timer that must keep running? Have u tried using a stopwatch app and see if stopping it will lost yr lap data?
reviews.author: Joshua Koh

reviews.title: Could be better...
reviews.comment: Hospital info can\'t be added. Might reinstall if this is fixed.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Needs fixing
reviews.comment: Worked perfectly when I used it the first time but after that it kept locking my phone whenever I tried to start timing my contractions....uninstall, I will be finding a different app which sucks cuz this one was the best one I had found so far... :(
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Excellent
reviews.comment: Helped me time my contractions and send them to my Doula. I was even able to show the doctor and nurses at the hospital. I recommend.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.comment: I would rate it better but still can\'t input hospital information.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.comment: This was a great program and now that the contacts are fixed its the perfect program. Thanks for all the hard work.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Daddy 511
reviews.comment: Fantastic app. Told us when to call midwife then when to leave for the hospital etc
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.comment: Cute app, but can\'t add hospital info.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.comment: Force closed the second time I tried opening...i have to have it.open tosave data....did not like.

reviews.title: Awesome!
reviews.comment: Thanks! One less thing I have to worry about on THE day. Best 511 app I\'ve seen, and I downloaded many.

reviews.comment: Labored at home & was able to have an unmedicated birth with the help of this app!

reviews.comment: Lots of bells and whistles, but 511 alert and averages don\'t work.

reviews.title: Awesome!
reviews.comment: The warning came up and we called the midwife immediately .   We weren\'t at 511 yet but the baby was coming anyways.  Didn\'t have time to make it to the hospital.   Unplanned homebirth worked out well.    Really saved the day.
reviews.author: Sasha Gagne

reviews.comment: Love this currently.. having contractions and it tells you when to go!!!
reviews.author: A Google User
